QUESTION STATEMENT - 1
What are the two values of the Boolean data type? How do you write them?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 1
THE TWO VALUES OF BOOLEAN DATA TYPE ARE (TRUE) AND (FALSE)


QUESTION STATEMENT - 2
What are the three different types of Boolean operators?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 2
THREE DIFFERENT TYPE OF BOOLEAN OPERATOR ARE 
1) AND (&&)
2) OR (||)
3) NOT (!)


QUESTION STATEMENT - 3
Make a list of each Boolean operator's truth tables (i.e. every possible combination of Boolean
values for the operator and what it evaluate ).

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 3
AND OPERATOR 

TRUE  TRUE  TRUE
FALSE FALSE FALSE
FALSE TRUE  FALSE
TRUE  FALSE FASLE

OR OPERATOR

TRUE  TRUE  TRUE
TRUE  FALSE TRUE
FALSE TRUE  TRUE 
FALSE FALSE FALSE

NOT OPERATOR

TRUE  TRUE  FALSE
TRUE  FALSE FALSE
FALSE TRUE  TRUE
FALSE FALSE TRUE 



QUESTION STATEMENT - 4
