(5 > 4) and (3 == 5)
not (5 > 4)
(5 > 4) or (3 == 5)
not ((5 > 4) or (3 == 5))
(True and True) and (True == False)
(not False) or (not True)

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 4
VALUE 1: FALSE
VALUE 2: FALSE
VALUE 3: TRUE
VALUE 4: FALSE
VALUE 5: FALSE
VALUE 6: TRUE3


QUESTION STATEMENT - 5
What are the six comparison operators?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 5
(==) FOR COMPARISON MEANS EQUAL TO
(!==) MEANS NOT EQUAL TO 
(>) MEANS GREATER THAN
(<) MEANS LESS THAN
(>=) MEANS GREATER THAM EQUAL TO 
(<=) MEANS LESS THAN EQUAL TO


QUESTION STATEMENT - 6
How do you tell the difference between the equal to and assignment operators?Describe a
condition and when you would use one.

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 6
SUPPOSE IF WE WANT TO ASSIGN ANY VALUE TO OUR VARIABLE WE WILL USE ASSIGNMENT OPERATOR (=) 
EXAMPLE : NAME = "SAHIL"
AND WE WANT TO VALIDATE OR CHECK OUR CONDITION WE WILL USE EQUAL TO OPERATOR (==)
EXAMPLE: NAME = "SAHIL" ; FIRST_NAME == NAME ; PRINT (" FIRST NAME AND NAME BOTH ARE SAME")


