QUESTION STATEMENT - 10
How can you tell the difference between break and continue?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 10
THE BASIC DIFFERENCE BETWEEN BREAK AND CONTIONUE IS WHEN WE USE BREAK KEYWORD INSIDE A LOOP AND IF THE CONDITION GETS SATISFIED THEN THE LOOP WILL NOT ITERATE TILL LAST ONCE CONDITION GETS SATISFIED THEN CONTROL WILL BE TRANSFERED OUTSIDE OF LOOP .
BUT WHEN WE USE CONTINUE KEYWORD IF THE CONDITION GETS SATISFIED THE LOOP WILL CONTINUE TO ITERATE TILL LAST. CONTINUE IS USED WHEN WE NEED SOME VARIABLE IMPLICITLY BUT WE DONT WANT TO APPLY ANY EXPRESSION ON IT.


QUESTION STATEMENT - 11
In a for loop, what is the difference between range(10), range(0, 10), and range(0, 10, 1)?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 11
WHEN WE WRITE range(10) WE WILL ITERATE TILL (N-1) INDEX THAT MEANS WE WILL ITERATE FROM 0-9 EXCLUDING 10.
WHEN WE WRITE range (0,10) WE WILL ITERATE FROM 0-9 EXCLUDING 10 SAME AS WE DID ABOVE HERE OLY DIFFERENCE IS THAT WE ARE SPECIFYING THE STARTING POINT AND ENDING POINT 
WHEN WE WRITE range(0,10,1) WE ARE ITERATING FROM 0-9 EXCLUDING 10. OBVIOUSLY RESULT WILL BE SAME BUT HERE WE MENTIONED STARTING POINT
ENDING POINT AND ALSO THE STEP SIZE THAT IS (1) IN OUR CASE.



QUESTION STATEMENT - 12
Write a short program that prints the numbers 1 to 10 using a for loop. Then write an equivalent
program that prints the numbers 1 to 10 using a while loop.

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 12
FOR LOOP 

a = 11
for i in range (1,11):
    print (i)

WHILE LOOP

a = 11
i=1
while i<=a:
    print (i)
    i=i+1


